58.4  ft 1
50.2 9 cu converging at either 50 11 40 or 5030 towards the apex between 47 m 154 ft 90 cu and 48 m 157 ft 92 cu high.378 The architects made a notable error in demarcating the base causing the southeast corner to extend 
1.5 8 m 
5.2  ft too far east. Consequently it is not square.57 A ditch was left in the pyramids north face during construction which allowed workers to build the inner corridor and chambers while the core was being erected around it before filling it in with rubble.2467 The pyramid is surrounded by a limestone paved courtyard except where the mortuary temple sits and is accessed from the temples north and south wings.68 Enclosing the courtyard is a tall rounded enclosure wall 
