14.9  m2 160 sq ft of space with the burial chamber to its west.4375 The chambers had a ceiling constructed from three gabled layers of limestone blocks2443 which dispersed the weight from the superstructure onto either side of the passageway preventing collapse.76 Perring estimated the largest blocks to be 
